The paper discusses the performance of a massive MIMO system in a mobile scenario, which involves channel estimation, signal processing, and communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the fundamental limits of communication and information processing. The paper also involves network infrastructure and wireless communication, which suggests the category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper uses a large number of antennas and users, which implies the category cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also considers the impact of mobility on the system performance, which suggests the category cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). Finally, the paper involves real-time processing and control, which suggests the category cs.SY (Systems and Control).
